answers.body_markdown:
**DataDirectory is an array of structs, not a pointer**.

[MSDN tells you][1] that the layout is actually 

    typedef struct _IMAGE_DATA_DIRECTORY {
        DWORD   VirtualAddress;
        DWORD   Size;
    } IMAGE_DATA_DIRECTORY, *PIMAGE_DATA_DIRECTORY;

and your .INC file just defines it as a QWORD for some unknown reason.

WinNT.h in the SDK defines the optional header as:

      ...
      DWORD   NumberOfRvaAndSizes;
      IMAGE_DATA_DIRECTORY DataDirectory[IMAGE_NUMBEROF_DIRECTORY_ENTRIES];
    } IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER32, *PIMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER32;

where `IMAGE_NUMBEROF_DIRECTORY_ENTRIES` is 16.

You should not just copy 16 items, the `NumberOfRvaAndSizes` member specifies the size and it could be &lt; 16.



  [1]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winnt/ns-winnt-image_data_directory
